1.title: Deus Ex Mommymus
1.plot: Upon learning that their mother has suddenly moved to Florida, Josh and Ian grapple with her terrifying ultimatum: get jobs or get out of my apartment.

2.title: Stripper Break
2.plot: After working diligently for several minutes trying to form their new company, Fire/Lightning Productions, Ian convinces Josh that they need a break...a stripper break.

3.title: Oops! Torture.
3.plot: After waking up early to get a head-start forming their entertainment company, Josh and Ian have a disastrous miscommunication trying to rectify their decision to let a creepy Fundamentalist Mormon into their apartment.

4.title: A Fundamentalist Mormon Visits
4.plot: After waking up early to get a head-start forming their entertainment company, Josh and Ian have a disastrous miscommunication trying to rectify their decision to let a creepy Fundamentalist Mormon into their apartment.

5.title: Tom Brady Cometh
5.plot: Upon receiving a final eviction notice from Mom, Josh and Ian struggle to figure out what to do next - Enter Tom Brady. Will he save the day?

imdb.plot outline: Josh and Ian have spent their post-college days (and months and years) blissfully holed up rent-free in their mother's house masturbating and watching Steven Seagal movies. But every Eden must fall. Upon learning that their mother has suddenly moved to Florida, the boys grapple with her terrifying ultimatum: get jobs or get out. In a blind panic, Josh seeks guidance from his man-bible, Tom Brady's autobiography "I Throw the Football: A Book about Me", which leads him to the best idea ever: take the entertainment world by storm. With no practical skills and dangerously short attention spans, what could possibly go wrong? Nothing.
